<TITLE> Daily Amar Desh editor gets bail in defamation case </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 9 (bdnews24.com)  Bangla daily Amar Desh acting editor Mahmudur Rahman has secured bail in a defamation suit filed by Tawfik-e-Elahi Chowdhury. Dhaka metropolitan magistrate SK Tofail Hasan gave the bail order on Tuesday after Rahman surrendered before the court and sought bail. With this, Rahman has secured bail in all the cases filed against him so far, his lawyers said. Amar Desh publisher Hashmat Ali and special correspondent M Abdullah also appeared before the court seeking bail. The bangla daily faced at least 20 cases for publishing a report on the prime minister's energy adviser Tawfik-e-Elahi and son Sajib Wazed Joy. Tawfik-e-Elahi filed the defamation suit against Rahman on January 19. Amar Desh in its December 17 issue had reported that Joy and Tawfik-e-Elahi allegedly took bribes to award US-based oil company Chevron a work order worth Tk 370 crore without floating tenders. b
